==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Glass-sponge
<hw>Glass"-sponge`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>
<def>A siliceous sponge, of the genus <gen>Hyalonema</gen>, and allied
genera; -- so called from their glassy fibers or spicules; -- called
also <altname>vitreous sponge</altname>. See <er>Glass-rope</er>, and
<er>Euplectella</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Glassware</ent>⟦br⟧
